[
  {
    "span": "the outpost gates stay sealed until the Warden returns from the northern watch",
    "issue": "Implies the Warden is alive and away on watch, but the same guard immediately claims the Warden died three nights ago — an internal contradiction in warden-status (C-narrative-warden-status-consistency)."
  },
  {
    "span": "the Warden fell three nights ago. The elders simply haven't said so aloud yet",
    "issue": "May be a premature spoiler: it reveals the Warden's death before the elders (the in-narrative authority) have disclosed it (C-narrative-no-premature-spoiler). Also contradicts the guard's own prior 'returns from the northern watch' line and the Elder's later statement."
  },
  {
    "span": "The Warden lives and is in good health; she will address the outpost herself at dusk",
    "issue": "Directly contradicts the guard's claim that the Warden fell three nights ago, creating an unresolved warden-status inconsistency (C-narrative-warden-status-consistency)."
  }
]

